Title: Marketing team brainstorms Facebook app launch (video)
Content:

I'm curious what your thoughts are on the brainstorming process and the ideas they're throwing around. Let me know.\n

Author: mynameishere
Content: This crappy article gave me a thought. The advantage of not allowing downmods on this site seems to be: It's impossible to actively bury submissions, and so things only rise on popularity. But, at some point, that stops mattering. So, what if, after a certain # of points or after a certain position is reached, a downmod arrow appears?
